  "technical_info": {
    "content": [
      "If you receive a PLAIN file you can use any number of free text editors to open the file. Notepad and Wordpad are bundled with Windows, while TextEdit is bundled with macOS.",
      "NOTE: You can change the \".plain\" extension to \".txt\" to make it a .TXT file."
    ]
  },
  "more_information": {
    "description": [
      "A PLAIN file is a plain text file that can be opened by any text editor. It contains plain text with no special formatting. PLAIN files may be used for a variety of purposes, such as storing a plain text version of a document, a copy of an email in HTML, or a receipt from a business."
    ]
